(377, 1, '2017-03-08 22:44:20', '2017-03-08 22:44:20', '[gallery link="none" ids="311,310,312"]\r\n\r\nTermites or white ants are the most harmful of the wood destroying pests. their activities are wide/spread throughout the country. they are also referred to as social insects. Their main colonies are usually located in the ground and from the nests. the termites make long galleries through the earth,possibly through the walls of buildings until they reach the wood work. It is obvious that the existence of termites in the soil will lead to much destruction of buildings and the woodwork. treating the entire floor area of a building at the time  of construction using sidual termiticide is the only answer to prevent their existence in the soil.\r\n\r\n<strong>Methods use to eliminate termites</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Drilling Treatment</strong>\r\n\r\nDrilling any slabs that is next to the home or business and inside the garage are a vital part of the termite treatment.\r\nThe reason for drilling these holes is to\r\nput the termiticide/insecticide under the slab where the termites can come into contact with the finished product.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-374" src="http://saran93.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/drill-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Soil injection  Treatment</strong>\r\n\r\nSoil treatments are liquid termiticides which ensure adequate coverage in the soil. Injection of this system in the soil creates a treated area that reduces the population of termites and envelops the structure with a long-term protection\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-375" src="http://saran93.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/inject-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Soil spray Treatment</strong>\r\n\r\nsoil treatments are often called termite “barriers”. Historically this came about as many of the older chemicals were repellent to termites. Termites coming into contact with this treated soil around the home would be repelled by the chemical, preventing them from entering the home – an invisible, protective “barrier”.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-376" src="http://saran93.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/spray-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" />', 'Termite Control', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '55-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-03-08 22:44:20', '2017-03-08 22:44:20', '', 55, 'http://saran93.co.nf/2017/03/08/55-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(378, 1, '2017-03-09 04:13:08', '2017-03-09 04:13:08', '<strong><span style="color: #000000;">Started in 2006. Our company is based on vision of providing our prospecting clients a high quality professional service promptly and at reasonably competitive charges. By providing a client - friendly, cost - effective service covered with a guarantee, our aim in the long run is to win our clients confidence and good - will for the control benefit of both parties. Our endeavour is to help create an environmental free from pests enabling the people of our country enjoy a healthy life</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #003366;"><strong>Our Vision </strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>To protect our valued, prospective clients, in particular, and all sri Lankan citizens, in general, from diverse problems arising due to pests, who cause various diseases and damage properties.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #003366;"><strong>Our Mission </strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>To provide an effective, cost/effective and environment-friendly safe service to control pests by adapting methods of modern treatment and technology, to safeguard health and property of our valued clientele.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #003366;"><strong>Our Goal </strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>To become the most reliable and recognized company in sri Lanka in the sphere of pest control by applying highest standards of professionalism and using ultra - modern developments in technology to wipe out successfully the pest menace from the country</strong></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #000080;"><strong><span style="color: #003366;">Our Organization</span> </strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="alignnone wp-image-339" src="http://saran93.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img779.jpg" alt="" width="109" height="150" />\r\n<strong>Mr.Lalith Chaminda Wijewardena </strong>\r\n<strong>Propritoer - Dene Pest Control Services</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="color: #000000;">We are a professional pest control organization with experience in th</span>is field. We adept the most acceptable scientific approach to control pests such as rats, cockroaches, ants, flies, mosquitoes, termites, etc... safety is our main concern &amp; therefore we use only safe household pesticides, recommended by the register of pesticides in srilanka. o</strong><strong>ur technical team is dedicated to control pests without polluting the environment and our company is backed by The Most Experienced Technical Staff In The Pest Control Sphere In Srilanka. We Are Geared With Up To Date equipment and also competent enough to prepare specific pesticides to solve any pest control problem at a short notice. </strong><strong>Our services include the controlling of pests in hotels, restaurants, catering establishments, hospitals, factories, ware-Houses, offices, residences, etc .., we undertake anti-termite soil treatment prior to construction of buildings and post-construction treatment to protect properly from the damage caused by termites(white-ants)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n</div>', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '42-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-03-09 04:13:08', '2017-03-09 04:13:08', '', 42, 'http://saran93.co.nf/2017/03/09/42-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
